    "registry/counterfactual-capture-patterns.json",
    "reviewed analysis",
    "generated candidate evidence",
    "legacy candidate material"
  ],
  "rules": [
    "The pinned upstream bytes control claims about public repository behavior.",
    "A source record identifies evidence but does not prove a derived claim without a locator and claim record.",
    "A claim status never changes the underlying source bytes.",
    "Inference-time processing, retention, training, telemetry, and strategic intent are separate propositions.",
    "Generated graphs, chunks, matches, and reports are candidate evidence only.",
    "Closed-system behavior remains Unknown until runtime, contractual, or other primary evidence resolves it.",
    "Counterfactual exposure patterns describe possible inference value and controls; they do not establish actual collection, retention, training, secondary use, or intent.",
    "Full SHA-256 chunk identities bind canonical preimages and immutable Git-blob spans; they do not promote semantic truth.",
    "The typed evidence graph is a deterministic projection. Similarity, connectivity, and centrality never promote claims or edges.",
    "Both .private/ and private/ are excluded custody paths and may never enter public builders or generated release artifacts.",
    "Iliad and Trojan-War material is outside the causal evidence chain; Move 37 is analogy and benchmark motivation only."
  ],
  "authoritative_files": {
    "method": "AGENTS.md",
    "upstream_identity": "UPSTREAM.lock.json",
    "source_metadata": "registry/source-registry.json",
    "repository_history_capture": "registry/repository-history-capture.json",
